static keywords can be used fot data members, methods and inner class (a class within a class)

static keyword cannot be used for local variables (declared within a method)
	Ex:
		class MyClass
		{
		   void ppp()
                   {
			static int n;//error - local variable cannot be static
                   }
		}

- static members are accessible directly with the classname without creating objects
- A static method can access only other static members directly
- A static variable acts as a global variable within class means all objects of the class can access
  static variable memory


Note: When a class is loaded by the JVM , java allocates memory for the static variables (without creating an object). Later , when an object is created, memory is allocated in heap for the instance variable with default calue. 
The good example of this is 


class Example {
    static int a;
    int b;

    void ppp() {
        a = 10;
        b = 20;
    }

    void display() {
        System.out.println("a: " + a + "b : " + b);

    }

}

public class StaitcDemo {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Example e1 = new Example();
        e1.ppp();
        e1.display();

        Example e2 = new Example();
        e2.display();
    }
}



here the value od e1.display will be 10 ,20   but e2 will be 10 ,0 

